    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="84"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CKS1" type="from">Chiang</persName> to President
                            <persName corresp="#p_RE1" type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d84fn1">Apparently sent to Washington via military channels,
                        and forwarded by the White House Map Room to <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> at Hyde Park.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-02">2 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>’s eyes only</p>
                <p>From the <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss> to his
                    Excellency President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>.</p>
                <p>I am in receipt of your telegrams transmitted to me by General <persName
                        corresp="#p_HTG1">Hearn</persName> on October 28th<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d84fn2">Dated October 27, 1943; <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_47">p. 47</ref>.</note> and 29th<note n="3" xml:id="d84fn3"
                        >Dated October 27, 1943. It concerned the signing of the Four-Nation
                        Declaration on General Security at the Moscow Conference of Foreign
                        Ministers.</note> and November 1st.<note n="4" xml:id="d84fn4">Dated October
                        30, 1943; <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_55">p.
                        55</ref>.</note> I am delighted to accept the suggestions contained in your
                    last telegram and am looking forward to meeting you and Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName>. Everything will be kept strictly
                    secret here….</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
